<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5886492>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Amusurgus (Amusurgus) fulvus Brunner von Wattenwyl, 1893 male from Singapore: head and pronotum in dorsal view (A), face in anterior view (B) and head and pronotum in lateral view (C), FW in dorsal view (D) and genitalia in dorsal view (E). Scale bar: 1 mm (for A–D)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5886492/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5886496>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Amusurgus (Amusurgus) xanthoneurus (Chopard, 1940) living female from Sandakan (Borneo: Sabah)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5886496/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5886488>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Amusurgus (Amusurgus) caerulus sp. nov. male (A–C) and female (D, E): head and pronotum in dorsal view (A, D), face in anterior view (B, E) and body in lateral view (C). Scale bars: 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5886488/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5886490>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Amusurgus (Amusurgus) caerulus sp. nov. male (A–D) and female (E, F): FW in dorsal view (A, E), abdominal apex of a living individual in ventral view (B), genitalia in ventral view (C) and posterior end of genitalia in dorsal view (D); and ovipositor in lateral view (F). Scale bar: 1 mm (for A, E, F)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5886490/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

